summary: OK YALL LETS GET ONE THING STRAIGHT
body:
OK YALL LETS GET ONE THING STRAIGHT

Into the Spider-verse is the best film I’ve seen all year and here’s why

  • ANIMATION?! BEUTIFUL?!
  • The music was epic.
  • Comedic timing was great
  • The plot line was so touching and beautiful I can’t
  • John Mulaney played Spiderham
  • the animation
  • Everything was beautiful
  • It was beautiful
  • ANAJSJDUUDUDYDYDYDYDYDYDYSYDYS
  • It was honestly so refreshing to see a movie that didn’t just pander to the algorithm
  • IT WAS SUPER PRETTY
  • SPIDER MAN

So anyways, conclusion-

Don’t watch vld season 8 and instead watch into the spider verse

summary: I'm not even going to lie, I actually cried a bit during Into the Spider-Verse. Like seeing the relationship between him and his...
body: I’m not even going to lie, I actually cried a bit during Into the Spider-Verse. Like seeing the relationship between him and his dad reminded me of the relationship I have with one of my own family members. And a whole bunch of other things that Miles goes through just reminded me of myself. Like I related to Miles a lot more than I expected to. And I think that’s what made me love this movie so much, cause I saw myself during his lowpoints of the movie, and it made me jump with joy when I saw him at his highpoints which made the little kid inside of me feel hopeful. And honestly, I’ve been needing something like a good Spider-Man movie to tell me that no matter how many times I get knocked down, that I need to always keep getting back up.
